text:
Freebsd version <= 9.x

wulf@fbsd91:/home/wulf % make love
Not war.

Freebsd version = 10

wulf@fbsd10:/home/wulf % make love
make: don't know how to make love. Stop

Fix: 

--- contrib/bmake/job.c	(revision 252094)
+++ contrib/bmake/job.c	(working copy)
@@ -1263,6 +1263,11 @@
 		(void)fflush(stdout);
   		return FALSE;
 	    } else {
+#ifndef WITHOUT_OLD_JOKE
+		if (strcmp(gn->name,"love") == 0)
+		    (*abortProc)("Not war.");
+		else                             
+#endif
 		(*abortProc)("%s%s %s. Stop", progname, msg, gn->name);
 		return FALSE;
 	    }
How-To-Repeat: type "make love" at shell prompt
